statements: SELECT * FROM facial_recognition_logs;
SELECT log_id, timestamp, user_id FROM facial_recognition_logs WHERE confidence_score > 0.8;
SELECT user_id, image_path FROM facial_recognition_logs WHERE detected_emotion = 'happy';
SELECT * FROM facial_recognition_logs WHERE user_id = 101 ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
SELECT detected_emotion, COUNT(*) AS count_emotions FROM facial_recognition_logs GROUP BY detected_emotion ORDER BY count_emotions DESC;
SELECT * FROM facial_recognition_logs WHERE confidence_score > 0.8 ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
SELECT user_id, detected_emotion, COUNT(*) as emotion_count FROM facial_recognition_logs GROUP BY user_id, detected_emotion ORDER BY emotion_count DESC;
SELECT user_id, AVG(confidence_score) as avg_confidence FROM facial_recognition_logs GROUP BY user_id HAVING avg_confidence > 0.5;
SELECT user_id, detected_emotion, MAX(confidence_score) as max_confidence FROM facial_recognition_logs GROUP BY user_id, detected_emotion;
SELECT user_id, image_path FROM facial_recognition_logs WHERE detected_emotion = 'happy' ORDER BY timestamp ASC LIMIT 5;

SELECT f.match_id, f.match_confidence, fr.person_name AS detected_person, fm.matched_person_id AS matched_person FROM face_matches fm JOIN faces_detected fd ON fm.detection_id = fd.detection_id JOIN facial_recognition_logs fr ON fd.log_id = fr.log_id WHERE fm.match_confidence > 0.7;

SELECT r.role_name, COUNT(ur.user_id) as total_users FROM roles r JOIN user_roles ur ON r.role_id = ur.role_id GROUP BY r.role_name;

SELECT u.username, a.access_type, ar.role_name FROM users u JOIN access_logs a ON u.user_id = a.user_id JOIN user_roles ur ON u.user_id = ur.user_id JOIN roles ar ON ur.role_id = ar.role_id WHERE a.timestamp >= '2022-01-01';
SELECT u.full_name, a.access_type FROM users u LEFT JOIN access_logs a ON u.user_id = a.user_id WHERE a.timestamp IS NULL;
